introduction: Height	5' 2" (1.57 m)Mini Bio (1)Georgia Tennant was born on December 25, 1984 in London, England as Georgia Elizabeth Moffett. She is an actress and producer, known for Staged (2020), Doctor Who: Dreamland (2009) and Bonkers (2007). She has been married to David Tennant since December 30, 2011. They have five children.Spouse (1)David Tennant	(30 December 2011 - present) ( 5 children)Trivia (19)She is the daughter of Peter Davison and Sandra Dickinson. Moffett is her father's actual surname, Davison being his stage name.After David Troughton (whose father was Patrick Troughton, the Second Doctor), she is the second child of an actor who played the Doctor (her father is Peter Davison, the Fifth Doctor) to have a speaking role in Doctor Who (1963) and/or Doctor Who (2005). She played the daughter of the Tenth Doctor (David Tennant) in Doctor Who: The Doctor's Daughter (2008), and in real-life in 2011 they married.She was born the day before her parents' sixth wedding anniversary.Has a tattoo of a star on her arm.In 2012, she made her West End debut, playing a secretary whom the main character tries to seduce and then has committed as insane, in the play "What the Butler Saw" by Joe Orton. Her husband, David Tennant, had acted in the same play 17 years, earlier. The 2012 production was not a critical or commercial success and was canceled two months into its run.Stepdaughter of Elizabeth Heery.Gave birth to her first child at age 17, a son named Tyler Peter Moffett, on March 27, 2002. Child's father is her now ex-boyfriend. The boy was adopted by her now-husband, David Tennant, in September 2011.In 2012, she changed her child-actor son's name by deed poll from Tyler Moffett to Ty Tennant (Tennant being her husband's stage name).Gave birth to her second child at age 26, a daughter named Olive Tennant, on March 29, 2011. Child's father is her then-boyfriend (now husband) David Tennant.(December 30, 2011) Married her boyfriend of three years
